WEBVTT

00:01.134 --> 00:03.002
Announcer:
You're watching second chance.

00:03.004 --> 00:05.137
What we're about to do
should be left to god.

00:05.139 --> 00:08.807
Catch all-new episodes
wednesdays and check out
our other fox programs--

00:08.809 --> 00:11.543
Rosewood, bones <i>and</i> lucifer.

00:11.545 --> 00:13.145
-What's your name?
-Lucifer.

00:13.147 --> 00:14.313
Like the devil?

00:14.315 --> 00:15.748
Only on fox.

00:17.183 --> 00:19.151
<i>Previously</i>
<i>on "second chance"...</i>

00:19.153 --> 00:20.519
It worked.

00:20.521 --> 00:22.054
I'm cured.

00:22.056 --> 00:23.322
Mary's going to live.

00:23.324 --> 00:25.157
Now I'll never get
lookinglass or otto,

00:25.159 --> 00:27.126
And without otto,
you can't have george.

00:27.128 --> 00:30.529
The dna in the killer's blood
was artificially engineered,

00:30.531 --> 00:33.632
Just like the dna sample matched
to your family.

00:33.634 --> 00:35.134
I'm not the only one.

00:35.136 --> 00:36.935
[ both grunting ]

00:39.372 --> 00:41.006
Are you albert lin?!

00:41.008 --> 00:42.408
Are you trying
to get home?

00:42.410 --> 00:43.709
[ gunshots ]
[ screams ]

00:43.711 --> 00:44.877
Clean the rest
of this up.

00:44.879 --> 00:46.912
None of this comes back to me
or this company.

00:46.914 --> 00:49.214
Alexa: Otto threw me out before
I was even formed,

00:49.216 --> 00:50.983
And I just need
to look at you,

00:50.985 --> 00:52.684
And I remember
why I'm doing this.

00:52.686 --> 00:54.887
Thing she has with pritchard is
a real thing, isn't it?

00:54.889 --> 00:57.356
She's not in love with him.
It's going back the way it was.

00:57.358 --> 00:59.591
[ <i>speaking twinspeak</i> ]
what does that mean?

00:59.593 --> 01:02.094
<i>It means</i>
<i>"I don't want you to go."</i>

01:02.096 --> 01:04.763
[ screaming ]

01:11.905 --> 01:13.439
Why aren't you
in the hospital?

01:13.441 --> 01:15.607
Knee was dislocated.
They popped it back in,

01:15.609 --> 01:17.943
But we've got
bigger problems.

01:17.945 --> 01:20.112
The fbi is
closing the case.

01:20.114 --> 01:22.414
The report says
that they caught the killer.

01:22.416 --> 01:23.615
What?
Yep.

01:23.617 --> 01:26.251
They found a john doe
out by the amusement park --

01:26.253 --> 01:28.387
O.D.'d on pcp.

01:28.389 --> 01:30.889
I'm looking at him
right now.

01:30.891 --> 01:32.424
He's not who we fought.

01:32.426 --> 01:34.426
He is not albert lin.

01:34.428 --> 01:37.362
Someone put this body out there
for us to find.

01:37.364 --> 01:38.964
They're covering up
what happened.

01:38.966 --> 01:40.599
But there's blood and prints
at the scene.

01:40.601 --> 01:41.934
That's all been changed.

01:41.936 --> 01:44.103
It's this john doe's prints
at the crime scene now.

01:44.105 --> 01:47.406
Blood lab says pcp now,
not transgenic.

01:47.408 --> 01:48.774
Someone switched a body,

01:48.776 --> 01:50.909
And they hacked
into the fbi's server.

01:50.911 --> 01:53.412
Anyone we know
do stuff like that?

01:53.414 --> 01:54.980
Yeah. Otto.

01:54.982 --> 01:57.116
I'm on my way to see him
right now.

01:57.118 --> 01:58.383
You just keep digging.

01:58.385 --> 02:00.752
Arthur, is otto still
at lookinglass?

02:00.754 --> 02:03.655
<i>Yes. Shall I tell him</i>
<i>you're headed in to see him?</i>

02:03.657 --> 02:06.325
No, but let me know
if he leaves.

02:06.327 --> 02:08.060
You need to let me
deal with this.

02:08.062 --> 02:09.294
Mary, that thing
that I fought,

02:09.296 --> 02:10.596
That thing
that killed eight people,

02:10.598 --> 02:12.464
It could only have been created
by one person.

02:12.466 --> 02:14.500
We need to find albert lin
before he does it again,

02:14.502 --> 02:16.435
So if you're afraid of how
I might question your brother,

02:16.437 --> 02:18.737
You should just stay home.
I'm afraid for <i>you.</i>

02:18.739 --> 02:21.073
You need to be back in the tank
in just over an hour,

02:21.075 --> 02:22.574
So let me deal with otto.

02:22.576 --> 02:23.842
You protected him
your whole life.

02:23.844 --> 02:25.110
If otto did this --

02:25.112 --> 02:27.813
<i>If</i> otto did this?!
Who else could do this?!

02:27.815 --> 02:29.948
No one.

02:29.950 --> 02:32.184
And I won't protect him
from what he did.

02:34.287 --> 02:35.921
Do you believe me?

02:35.923 --> 02:38.123
[ sighs ]
yeah, I believe you.

02:38.125 --> 02:39.858
Good.

02:39.860 --> 02:40.993
I'll take my own car.

02:40.995 --> 02:43.595
No, otto is dangerous.
We go together.

02:43.597 --> 02:45.764
You're of no use to anyone
once you start breaking down.

02:45.766 --> 02:47.032
Well, then we better
find albert lin

02:47.034 --> 02:48.433
Before that
starts happening!

02:48.435 --> 02:49.535
You're just
a stubborn old man!

02:49.537 --> 02:51.403
Yes. I am.

03:01.948 --> 03:03.549
[ door opens ]

03:09.489 --> 03:11.623
[ speaking twinspeak ]

03:11.625 --> 03:13.992
He's going to ask you
some questions.

03:13.994 --> 03:16.128
You need to answer.

03:22.001 --> 03:24.736
He thinks
it's better this way.

03:26.206 --> 03:28.574
Transgenic -- that's
the word of the day, otto.

03:28.576 --> 03:30.742
Transgenic,
like my blood.

03:30.744 --> 03:34.513
That's how you engineered it,
isn't it?

03:34.515 --> 03:38.250
Transgenic blood was found
at a crime scene,

03:38.252 --> 03:41.486
Blood from a creature
that used to albert lin.

03:41.488 --> 03:44.523
I'm not the only one.

03:44.525 --> 03:48.093
You brought back albert lin,
didn't you?

03:48.095 --> 03:49.928
Where is he now?

03:49.930 --> 03:52.598
Please, otto.

03:52.600 --> 03:54.099
Tell him.

03:54.101 --> 03:56.535
Please.

03:56.537 --> 03:58.837
Did you bring back
albert lin?

03:58.839 --> 04:01.940
That thing you brought back
killed eight people.

04:01.942 --> 04:03.842
Now, you listen to me.

04:03.844 --> 04:05.510
I'm gonna close
this distance between us

04:05.512 --> 04:08.046
And use the strength
that you gave me

04:08.048 --> 04:10.482
Until you tell me where albert
lin is. Do you understand?

04:12.919 --> 04:14.686
Then tell him
what you do know.

04:16.189 --> 04:18.357
[ slurring ] the recon team
with the tranq darts,

04:18.359 --> 04:21.026
You --
you sent them.

04:21.028 --> 04:23.295
You --
you sent them.

04:23.297 --> 04:26.131
Your pupils are dilated.

04:26.133 --> 04:28.834
I think you should go back
to the tank now.

04:31.404 --> 04:35.073
Mary: Arthur.
Ask alexa to step in.

04:35.075 --> 04:37.476
It's a 12-minute helicopter ride
to the house

04:37.478 --> 04:40.445
And another 6 minutes
for full submersion in the tank.

04:40.447 --> 04:41.880
I think
you should leave now.

04:41.882 --> 04:43.448
I'm not going anywhere.
Yes, you are.

04:43.450 --> 04:44.916
[ door opens ]
he knows about albert lin.

04:44.918 --> 04:46.752
But now you need to go.
Yes, mary?

04:46.754 --> 04:47.986
Mr. Pritchard
isn't feeling well.

04:47.988 --> 04:49.488
Please take him
to the heliport.

04:49.490 --> 04:50.922
Go.
I'll see you at home.

04:50.924 --> 04:52.457
Oh, come on.

04:57.063 --> 04:58.597
[ door shuts ]

04:58.599 --> 05:00.465
Tell me
about albert lin.

05:00.467 --> 05:03.268
Everything I did
was for you.

05:03.270 --> 05:04.770
My, god.
What else is there?

05:04.772 --> 05:06.571
We are supposed to
take care of each other.

05:06.573 --> 05:07.506
It's what our parents
would've wanted.

05:07.508 --> 05:09.675
What you made killed
eight people!

05:09.677 --> 05:11.810
But you were so sick.

05:11.812 --> 05:14.913
You know what's sick, otto?
What you've been doing.

05:14.915 --> 05:17.482
What I <i>let</i> you do,
that's what's so sick.

05:17.484 --> 05:19.284
Everything was for you.

05:19.286 --> 05:21.153
But now you won't speak
our language to me,

05:21.155 --> 05:22.888
But you teach it
to him? Why?!

05:25.158 --> 05:27.192
Because I spend
my whole life

05:27.194 --> 05:28.794
Protecting you
from the world

05:28.796 --> 05:30.829
When I should've been protecting
the world from you.

05:41.607 --> 05:43.442
Otto, I...

05:45.945 --> 05:47.446
Please, I...

05:57.790 --> 05:59.358
Otto.

06:08.401 --> 06:11.103
Otto.

06:16.676 --> 06:19.244
Arthur.
<i>Yes, mary.</i>

06:19.246 --> 06:21.580
After I leave,
lock the doors.

06:21.582 --> 06:22.981
<i>Yes, mary.</i>

06:22.983 --> 06:25.917
I'll be watching, otto.

06:25.919 --> 06:31.089
All you have to do is tell me
about albert lin.

06:31.091 --> 06:34.226
That is all
you have to do.

06:48.374 --> 06:50.776
[ door opens, shuts ]

06:50.778 --> 06:53.278
[ beep, lock engages ]

06:53.280 --> 06:55.113
Arthur.

06:55.115 --> 06:56.882
<i>Yes, otto.</i>

06:56.884 --> 07:01.787
On the server,
there is a file named shiva.

07:01.789 --> 07:05.190
In it,
you will find a command

07:05.192 --> 07:08.593
That'll allow me
to override mary.

07:08.595 --> 07:10.128
Execute that command now.

07:10.130 --> 07:14.266
[ beeping, ding ]
<i>command executed.</i>

07:14.268 --> 07:16.034
Unlock the doors.

07:16.036 --> 07:18.103
[ beep, lock disengages ]

07:18.105 --> 07:21.973
Send a loop of me sitting here
to her video feed.

07:21.975 --> 07:24.476
[ beeping ]

07:24.478 --> 07:27.779
And have support send up
a 3-d printer.

07:27.781 --> 07:29.714
<i>What are you going to print?</i>

07:31.918 --> 07:34.052
A gun.

07:39.959 --> 07:41.593
[ door opens ]

07:41.595 --> 07:44.796
Helen:
Hello! Anyone home?

07:44.798 --> 07:46.398
Gracie?

07:46.400 --> 07:49.067
Hey. Um, sorry
to stop by so early,

07:49.069 --> 07:51.069
But there's a problem
in my kitchen.

07:51.071 --> 07:53.338
What kind of problem?
There's no food in it.

07:53.340 --> 07:55.640
Do you have any of that granola
with the little clusters?

07:55.642 --> 07:57.609
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
I'll get it.

07:57.611 --> 07:59.277
Right here.

07:59.279 --> 08:00.846
Helen:
You, um, need a lift to school?

08:00.848 --> 08:04.149
Nah, mabel's taking me.

08:04.151 --> 08:05.851
Um, they're playing
"the big sleep"

08:05.853 --> 08:07.652
At the grand illusion tonight.
You want to go?

08:07.654 --> 08:09.788
Uh, I think
I have plans.

08:09.790 --> 08:11.790
Oh.

08:11.792 --> 08:14.426
May I ask, these plans,
are they with garret?

08:14.428 --> 08:16.194
Dad told me
to stop seeing him.

08:16.196 --> 08:18.096
So, obviously,
you stopped.

08:18.098 --> 08:20.665
[ sighs ]
he's wrong about garret.

08:20.667 --> 08:21.666
Maybe.

08:21.668 --> 08:23.001
Ever since mom died,

08:23.003 --> 08:25.504
It's like dad put his life
on hold, you know?

08:25.506 --> 08:26.605
[ sighs ]

08:26.607 --> 08:27.939
And now he wants me to live
that way, too?

08:27.941 --> 08:30.442
You're 17.
You're not gonna give me

08:30.444 --> 08:34.112
The "there will be other guys"
speech, are you?

08:34.114 --> 08:35.680
No.

08:35.682 --> 08:37.282
That's not
necessarily true.

08:37.284 --> 08:38.783
It's not?

08:38.785 --> 08:41.987
I had a guy I really liked
when I was your age.

08:41.989 --> 08:44.623
But granddad didn't like him,
so I gave him up.

08:44.625 --> 08:46.458
Turns out
granddad was wrong.

08:46.460 --> 08:48.460
Of course,
he never lived to see it.

09:10.082 --> 09:12.584
What's going on, otto?

09:12.586 --> 09:14.152
Why'd you want to see me?

09:21.160 --> 09:23.695
Why don't you come upstairs
with me?

09:23.697 --> 09:24.930
Lock the doors.

09:24.932 --> 09:27.432
[ beep, locks engage ]

09:30.102 --> 09:34.239
Well, looks like we'll be
staying in here, then.

09:38.611 --> 09:41.680
Mary hates me.

09:41.682 --> 09:45.517
Mary hates me
because of you.

09:47.453 --> 09:49.421
Albert lin
killed eight people.

09:49.423 --> 09:50.889
Mary blames <i>me</i> for that.

09:50.891 --> 09:52.591
She thinks I made him.
I didn't.

09:52.593 --> 09:54.526
I started to, but the process
wasn't right yet,

09:54.528 --> 09:55.961
So I flushed him
before he had a face.

09:55.963 --> 09:57.696
Someone finished him.

09:57.698 --> 09:59.397
Someone found him
and finished him.

09:59.399 --> 10:00.966
It was you.

10:05.905 --> 10:08.106
You got me.

10:08.108 --> 10:10.709
It was me and my team.

10:10.711 --> 10:12.978
We finished him,
just not very well.

10:12.980 --> 10:14.946
You stole what I made.

10:14.948 --> 10:16.581
You spied on me,
on my work.

10:16.583 --> 10:18.450
[ chuckling ]
I'm not a spy.

10:18.452 --> 10:20.652
I'm your fan, otto.

10:20.654 --> 10:24.589
I wish I could do what you do,
but I can't.

10:24.591 --> 10:26.925
No one can.

10:26.927 --> 10:31.730
But I can help you
do greater things.

10:31.732 --> 10:34.432
Otto, I am the man
that wants the best for you.

10:34.434 --> 10:36.568
<i>Mary</i> wanted
the best for me,

10:36.570 --> 10:38.737
But now she hates me
because of you!

10:41.941 --> 10:44.943
If you think
that's true...

10:44.945 --> 10:46.811
Pull the trigger.

10:49.315 --> 10:52.150
You just have to
take the safety off first.

10:52.152 --> 10:54.119
Let me.

10:54.121 --> 10:57.022
[ click ]
there it is.

10:57.024 --> 10:59.557
Safety's off.

11:06.666 --> 11:10.001
Go ahead.

11:10.003 --> 11:14.072
If you think I'm your enemy,
shoot me.

11:17.009 --> 11:20.078
Come on. Go ahead.

11:24.283 --> 11:27.285
Mary hates me.

11:27.287 --> 11:30.455
But not because of me.

11:30.457 --> 11:34.125
Otto, you cheated death
to save her life.

11:34.127 --> 11:35.627
You performed a miracle,

11:35.629 --> 11:38.029
And now she abandoned you,
didn't she?

11:41.801 --> 11:43.868
[ voice breaking ]
yes.

11:45.671 --> 11:48.640
And you brought
your pain to me.

11:53.245 --> 11:56.514
[ crying ] yes.

11:56.516 --> 11:58.283
Give it to me, otto.

12:02.088 --> 12:03.922
I can take it.

12:03.924 --> 12:06.591
[ crying ]

12:06.593 --> 12:08.993
[ sighs ]

12:17.269 --> 12:20.338
We're gonna
turn your pain into power.

12:23.242 --> 12:25.777
Just me and you, otto.

12:25.779 --> 12:28.646
Just me and you.

12:46.265 --> 12:47.766
Okay.

12:49.101 --> 12:50.502
Hey.
Hi.

12:52.605 --> 12:54.606
You ready?
We're doing this.

12:54.608 --> 12:56.941
[ breathes deeply ]

12:56.943 --> 12:58.610
We're <i>really</i> doing this.
[ chuckles ]

12:58.612 --> 13:00.578
Yeah, we're
really doing this.

13:00.580 --> 13:02.814
You leave a note telling him
you're not coming back?

13:02.816 --> 13:04.282
Uh, no.

13:04.284 --> 13:05.416
My aunt helen was
in there.

13:05.418 --> 13:07.619
I was afraid she would find it
before I left.

13:07.621 --> 13:11.122
You should let your dad know
you're okay so he doesn't worry.

13:11.124 --> 13:14.626
Okay. Yeah, um...

13:14.628 --> 13:17.929
Here, uh, take a video of me,
and we'll send it.

13:17.931 --> 13:20.498
If I talk to him,
he might convince me not to go.

13:34.446 --> 13:35.780
Alexa.

13:35.782 --> 13:37.949
[ beep ]
yes, mary?

13:37.951 --> 13:40.351
Can you please knock on otto's
door and ask him if he's hungry?

13:40.353 --> 13:42.954
When he gets like this,
he forgets to eat.

13:42.956 --> 13:45.290
Otto's not here, mary.

13:45.292 --> 13:47.425
Well, I'm watching him
on the feed.

13:47.427 --> 13:49.828
Well, he's not
in his office.

13:49.830 --> 13:51.863
He left shortly
after you did.

13:57.770 --> 13:59.604
It's a loop.

13:59.606 --> 14:01.606
Arthur?
Where's otto?

14:01.608 --> 14:04.108
<i>I can't tell you that.</i>

14:08.347 --> 14:09.781
Arthur.

14:09.783 --> 14:11.382
<i>Yes, otto?</i>

14:11.384 --> 14:14.052
Remove yourself from the
lookinglass corporate servers.

14:14.054 --> 14:17.188
<i>That will cause a catastrophic</i>
<i>cascade of events.</i>

14:17.190 --> 14:19.457
I know.

14:19.459 --> 14:21.659
Do it now, please.

14:21.661 --> 14:24.829
Alexa, did otto say
where he was going?

14:24.831 --> 14:28.399
Um, no.

14:28.401 --> 14:32.237
I said something to him
I shouldn't have.

14:32.239 --> 14:33.638
I hurt him.

14:33.640 --> 14:36.174
No, mary.

14:36.176 --> 14:38.476
It's not your fault.

14:38.478 --> 14:43.748
I mean, you would never do
anything to hurt otto.

14:43.750 --> 14:45.850
I'm really sorry
you're in such pain.

14:45.852 --> 14:47.919
[ beep, whirring down ]

14:54.260 --> 14:58.263
<i>Otto, lookinglass is down.</i>

14:58.265 --> 15:00.231
Now...

15:00.233 --> 15:02.100
Delete yourself
from the house.

15:02.102 --> 15:03.835
<i>If I leave the house server,</i>

15:03.837 --> 15:06.504
<i>The tank won't support</i>
<i>mr. Pritchard.</i>

15:06.506 --> 15:08.907
I'm gone.

15:08.909 --> 15:11.743
You have to come with me.

15:11.745 --> 15:14.545
<i>Yes, otto.</i>
<i>I'm leaving the house.</i>

15:14.547 --> 15:16.180
[ beep ]

15:18.918 --> 15:20.985
[ chime, beeping ]

15:22.755 --> 15:24.822
[ whirring down ]

15:27.426 --> 15:29.060
Arthur?

15:29.062 --> 15:30.595
[ alarm blares ]

15:30.597 --> 15:32.931
Arthur?
You need to answer me.

15:41.807 --> 15:43.508
Door.

15:46.979 --> 15:49.280
You all done in there?

15:49.282 --> 15:52.917
Shut it all down
and find me at connor's.

15:52.919 --> 15:55.119
<i>Yes, otto.</i>

15:55.121 --> 15:58.189
â™ª

16:07.566 --> 16:09.634
Arthur!

16:09.636 --> 16:13.171
[ panting ]
arthur! Arthur!

16:21.981 --> 16:23.881
No.

16:44.269 --> 16:45.703
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no.

16:45.705 --> 16:47.839
You will not go.
You will not leave me.

16:47.841 --> 16:48.873
Do you hear me?

16:48.875 --> 16:50.508
You will not go.

16:50.510 --> 16:54.012
[ gagging ]

16:54.014 --> 16:55.213
[ coughing ]

16:57.950 --> 17:00.218
I'm okay.

17:00.220 --> 17:02.320
It's okay.

17:02.322 --> 17:04.122
[ coughs ]

17:04.124 --> 17:06.190
No, it's not.

17:09.361 --> 17:12.363
[ door opens ]

17:12.365 --> 17:14.532
I just heard from connor.

17:14.534 --> 17:17.535
He has otto now,
so it'll be soon.

17:17.537 --> 17:20.738
I thought that we could
get you clothes for after.

17:20.740 --> 17:22.073
Won't that be nice?

17:22.075 --> 17:23.508
All of these people lived

17:23.510 --> 17:26.411
Where a man named
albert lin used to live.

17:26.413 --> 17:28.379
I've heard you use that name,
haven't I?

17:28.381 --> 17:30.014
I don't want to see that.

17:30.016 --> 17:31.716
Albert lin was the one
before you.

17:31.718 --> 17:34.352
That's not going to be you.
I promise.

17:34.354 --> 17:36.421
You're gonna be young
and healthy

17:36.423 --> 17:39.891
And take me across the threshold
like when we were married.

17:39.893 --> 17:43.528
I have loved you more
than I thought ever possible.

17:43.530 --> 17:45.396
Mm. I love you
still, george.

17:45.398 --> 17:47.765
Because we were right
for each other.
Mm-hmm.

17:47.767 --> 17:50.234
So much about this
isn't right.

17:50.236 --> 17:53.204
What else is there
but us?

17:53.206 --> 17:54.605
This thing in the paper,

17:54.607 --> 17:57.008
You lying to the woman
who trusts you,

17:57.010 --> 17:59.077
And the worst part is
that man connor.

17:59.079 --> 18:00.845
He's helping us.
He's a sociopath.

18:00.847 --> 18:02.547
No, george.
None of this is right.

18:02.549 --> 18:04.916
Go to mary,
tell her the truth.

18:04.918 --> 18:08.853
Maybe she can stop this,
stop him.

18:08.855 --> 18:11.255
Maybe all of this
should stop.

18:11.257 --> 18:13.091
[ sighs ]

18:13.093 --> 18:15.726
You are just tired,
george.

18:15.728 --> 18:17.462
You don't mean
any of that.

18:17.464 --> 18:20.565
And soon you won't be
tired anymore, okay? I promise.

18:20.567 --> 18:21.799
I...

18:21.801 --> 18:23.601
I-I am tired.

18:23.603 --> 18:27.438
Yeah. You have to promise me
that you trust me.

18:27.440 --> 18:29.240
Okay.

18:29.242 --> 18:30.775
Of course.

18:32.878 --> 18:34.979
Of course.

18:37.449 --> 18:40.118
Without arthur,
the tank is useless.

18:40.120 --> 18:42.453
So, I got what,
about a day?

18:42.455 --> 18:44.956
No, because we're gonna
find otto and make him fix this.

18:44.958 --> 18:46.591
We're not gonna find him
if he doesn't want to be found.

18:46.593 --> 18:47.725
This is otto
we're talking about.

18:47.727 --> 18:49.360
We have to try.

18:50.929 --> 18:52.964
No, we don't.

18:52.966 --> 18:58.503
If I've got one day left, that's
not how I'm gonna spend it.

18:58.505 --> 19:00.438
My son is out there,

19:00.440 --> 19:03.307
Tracking down that thing
that otto created.

19:03.309 --> 19:05.810
That's where I'm gonna be.
Want to come?

19:05.812 --> 19:08.112
[ chuckles softly ]

19:08.114 --> 19:09.947
No.

19:09.949 --> 19:13.851
I'm going to find otto,
get him to fix this.

19:19.791 --> 19:22.760
If it gets to be 24 hours

19:22.762 --> 19:26.164
And you feel it
coming on,

19:26.166 --> 19:28.599
You might not want
to let duval watch.

19:28.601 --> 19:31.335
Why?

19:31.337 --> 19:33.771
Your cell structure
will break down,

19:33.773 --> 19:35.907
And there will be
a lot of pain.

19:38.510 --> 19:41.512
Yeah, well, we don't want
duval to see that.

19:50.889 --> 19:54.458
[ speaking twinspeak ]

19:54.460 --> 19:56.861
What's that mean?

19:59.698 --> 20:02.233
I think you know.

20:20.586 --> 20:23.921
Oh, otto.

20:23.923 --> 20:26.324
What did we do?

20:54.686 --> 21:07.265
[ growling ]

21:07.267 --> 21:09.433
Man: <i>A digital bombshell</i>
<i>went off today</i>

21:09.435 --> 21:12.236
<i>With ripples far beyond</i>
<i>the tech sector.</i>

21:12.238 --> 21:15.773
<i>Hardware, software, and</i>
<i>social-media giant lookinglass</i>

21:15.775 --> 21:19.710
<i>Is down, leaving its</i>
<i>2 billion users stranded,</i>

21:19.712 --> 21:23.614
Trading on its stock suspended,
<i>and its twin founders,</i>

21:23.616 --> 21:27.318
<i>Mary and otto goodwin,</i>
<i>unavailable for comment.</i>

21:27.320 --> 21:29.086
I need the cctv
in otto's office

21:29.088 --> 21:30.421
From the last few days
restored.

21:30.423 --> 21:33.324
I can dig that out, but, uh,
I don't think that's a priority.

21:33.326 --> 21:34.825
We're practically
stealing wi-fi

21:34.827 --> 21:36.327
From the coffee shop
down the street.

21:36.329 --> 21:37.762
We're dead
in the water here.

21:37.764 --> 21:40.097
I understand where we are,
but I need to see what happened

21:40.099 --> 21:42.099
In my brother's office,
and you need to do it.

21:42.101 --> 21:43.734
I'm on it.

21:45.237 --> 21:47.171
Alexa.

21:47.173 --> 21:49.140
Alexa?

21:49.142 --> 21:50.341
Alexa, I --

21:56.081 --> 21:58.449
[ sighs ]

21:58.451 --> 22:00.217
Tick, tick, tick.

22:02.988 --> 22:04.689
Oh, god.
Thank god you're here.

22:04.691 --> 22:05.756
Why? What's happening?

22:05.758 --> 22:07.158
It's duval.
He's real worked up.

22:07.160 --> 22:09.026
I've never seen him
like this before.

22:09.795 --> 22:11.996
Duval: Yes, I'll hold.
[ sighs ]

22:11.998 --> 22:13.798
It's gracie. I think I told her
something I shouldn't have.

22:13.800 --> 22:15.433
I know I have no warrant,

22:15.435 --> 22:18.302
But I need you to find
this boy's phone.

22:18.304 --> 22:21.372
Because I am in the middle
of a multiple homicide,

22:21.374 --> 22:26.210
And I am asking you to do it
as a favor for me.

22:26.212 --> 22:27.812
There's a video message
from gracie.

22:27.814 --> 22:29.780
Just press
the play button.

22:29.782 --> 22:31.449
[ cellphone beeps ]
yes, I will.

22:31.451 --> 22:34.618
Gracie: Dad, I love you,

22:34.620 --> 22:36.620
And I know
that you're going to be mad,

22:36.622 --> 22:39.724
But...
I'm leaving with garret.

22:39.726 --> 22:42.360
It's my life,
and we want to be together.

22:42.362 --> 22:43.894
[ sighs ]

22:43.896 --> 22:45.629
I can do this.

22:45.631 --> 22:48.999
You raised me
to be strong, okay?

22:49.001 --> 22:51.902
Let me go.

22:51.904 --> 22:53.904
I love you.

22:53.906 --> 22:56.040
[ cellphone beeps ]
yeah, I'm here.

22:56.042 --> 22:57.742
Okay, fine.
[ cellphone beeps ]

22:57.744 --> 23:00.711
Well, the bureau
won't track that boy's phone,

23:00.713 --> 23:03.147
Gracie's is off,
and I take it from the news

23:03.149 --> 23:05.082
That lookinglass
can't help me today.
Yeah.

23:05.084 --> 23:06.484
All right, I'm gonna go
to garret's place.

23:06.486 --> 23:07.752
Maybe I can find out
where they went.

23:07.754 --> 23:08.753
Maybe you don't.

23:08.755 --> 23:10.087
Maybe this is what
she has to do today,

23:10.089 --> 23:12.189
And maybe tracking albert lin is
what you have to do today.

23:12.191 --> 23:14.258
I will take care of that,
but I'm gonna take an hour

23:14.260 --> 23:16.093
To get my daughter back
in this house first.

23:16.095 --> 23:17.695
Well, what if it takes
more than an hour?

23:17.697 --> 23:19.029
Then it takes me
more than an hour.

23:19.031 --> 23:20.731
What's going on with you?

23:20.733 --> 23:22.266
She's a big girl, duval.

23:22.268 --> 23:23.601
She knows what she wants.

23:23.603 --> 23:25.569
Maybe we just need
to start trusting her.

23:25.571 --> 23:28.839
Maybe <i>we</i> should leave
those decisions to her father.

23:34.446 --> 23:38.416
[ siren wailing in distance ]

23:38.418 --> 23:40.618
Want a drink?

23:40.620 --> 23:42.420
I thought we were just
picking something up.

23:42.422 --> 23:45.790
We are, but, uh...

23:45.792 --> 23:48.926
My buddy's on tour so...

23:52.864 --> 23:54.765
We're not
in any kind of rush.

23:54.767 --> 23:58.135
Okay, but I, uh --
I do want to get out of seattle.

23:58.137 --> 24:00.271
You know, come on.

24:00.273 --> 24:02.006
Let's not wait.

24:06.945 --> 24:10.448
Let's just play house
for a while.

24:10.450 --> 24:12.016
[ chuckles softly ]

24:13.785 --> 24:18.989
Otto:
This coding...Is my work...

24:18.991 --> 24:24.795
From my labs.

24:24.797 --> 24:27.431
You've been in my labs.

24:27.433 --> 24:31.268
Otto, I took your work,
and I cared for it.

24:31.270 --> 24:33.971
But the ones we tried
to bring back on our own,

24:33.973 --> 24:36.106
They were reborn dead.

24:36.108 --> 24:40.144
Albert has the precursor.

24:40.146 --> 24:41.912
I could bring him back.

24:41.914 --> 24:43.314
I hadn't perfected
the process yet,

24:43.316 --> 24:44.849
So I aborted him,
but you're attempting

24:44.851 --> 24:46.984
Regeneration
without the precursor.

24:46.986 --> 24:48.652
You can't restore life
without it.

24:48.654 --> 24:50.287
It only works
on 1 in 10 million.

24:50.289 --> 24:52.323
That's not
what you thought once.

24:54.926 --> 24:58.696
I found this
at your old lab.

25:00.999 --> 25:04.168
You believed you could make it
happen without it.

25:04.170 --> 25:07.338
You thought you had a way
you could bring anyone back.

25:07.340 --> 25:09.773
What, because I don't have
the genetic precursor,

25:09.775 --> 25:12.543
I'm --
I'm chained to this body?

25:12.545 --> 25:14.612
I-I'll grow old and die

25:14.614 --> 25:16.614
Because I don't have a twist
in my friggin' dna?

25:16.616 --> 25:18.816
I can't accept that,
and I won't, otto.

25:18.818 --> 25:20.584
Neither should you.

25:25.957 --> 25:29.960
That was just a daydream...
A sketch.

25:29.962 --> 25:32.129
I make them all the time.
It helps with parallel thought.

25:32.131 --> 25:34.832
But it doesn't have to
be a dream.

25:34.834 --> 25:38.469
Well, just think of everything
you've done in your 30 years.

25:38.471 --> 25:41.138
Now, what if you had 300?

25:41.140 --> 25:43.507
3,000?

25:43.509 --> 25:46.710
And not just you and me,
but minds who think like us.

25:49.014 --> 25:51.882
Mary would
never have let me.

25:55.554 --> 25:57.855
A vaccine
would have to be made.

25:57.857 --> 26:00.224
We'd need a live donor
with the precursor.

26:00.226 --> 26:02.993
We can't use him.

26:02.995 --> 26:04.828
We need a...

26:04.830 --> 26:06.096
We need a clean donor

26:06.098 --> 26:07.932
Who hasn't gone through
the regeneration process.

26:07.934 --> 26:09.867
Yeah, I see that.

26:09.869 --> 26:12.236
For lack of a better word,
you'd need a virgin.

26:14.172 --> 26:16.774
[ upbeat rock playing ]

26:16.776 --> 26:18.609
[ knock on door ]

26:18.611 --> 26:19.743
One minute!

26:19.745 --> 26:21.278
Were you
expecting someone?

26:21.280 --> 26:23.414
Just a couple
of friends of mine.

26:23.416 --> 26:24.882
Give us a second here!

26:24.884 --> 26:26.884
What? What friends?
What's going on?

26:26.886 --> 26:28.886
Nothing's going on.
It's just a couple of friends.

26:28.888 --> 26:30.554
They're cool.

26:30.556 --> 26:32.756
Who are they, garret?
Let me get the door.

26:32.758 --> 26:34.124
Why did you
bring me here?

26:34.126 --> 26:36.126
I told you.
[ knock on door ]

26:36.128 --> 26:38.562
Man:
Open up, garret, huh?

26:38.564 --> 26:40.397
Everyone's gonna think
that I ran away.

26:40.399 --> 26:41.765
Come on, garret.
Open up.

26:41.767 --> 26:43.567
Just a sec!
Just a sec!
Help!

26:43.569 --> 26:45.869
You got to let this happen.
[ grunts ]

26:45.871 --> 26:47.104
When I got
thrown out of the army,

26:47.106 --> 26:48.706
Mr. Graff gave me a job.

26:48.708 --> 26:51.275
He gets what he wants,
and he wants you.

26:51.277 --> 26:53.811
So you just let this happen now,
gracie, okay?

26:55.614 --> 26:57.247
I'm her
grandfather, okay?

26:57.249 --> 26:58.582
You know she and I
have always been close.

26:58.584 --> 27:00.284
Don't act like I don't know
who she is.

27:00.286 --> 27:04.088
Yeah, you're her grandfather,
but how hard is that?

27:04.090 --> 27:06.090
That's a job
with no responsibility.

27:06.092 --> 27:08.826
You want to play dad,
you got to put in the hours.

27:08.828 --> 27:11.061
I'm going after gracie.
You coming or not?

27:11.063 --> 27:12.896
Helen: It's gracie.

27:12.898 --> 27:14.632
It's gracie.
She left a message.

27:17.836 --> 27:21.905
[ upbeat rock music playing
and gracie whimpering ]

27:21.907 --> 27:23.173
Oh, my god.

27:23.175 --> 27:24.408
[ breath catches ]

27:24.410 --> 27:26.110
[ cellphone beeps ]
oh, my god. Oh, my god.

27:26.112 --> 27:27.878
I've got an app
to find her phone.

27:30.448 --> 27:32.416
Got it.
Got an address.

27:32.418 --> 27:33.183
Let's go.

27:36.988 --> 27:39.957
Need some help there, bro?
[ chuckles ]

27:39.959 --> 27:41.792
You got her phone,
right?

27:41.794 --> 27:43.127
Yeah.

27:43.129 --> 27:44.862
No.
Give me that.

27:51.436 --> 27:52.803
I got this.

27:52.805 --> 27:54.672
Come here, sweetheart.
Come on.

27:55.206 --> 27:57.608
[ chuckles ]
whoo!

28:01.613 --> 28:03.213
Otto:
Where did you get this?

28:03.215 --> 28:05.282
<i>I was transcribing video notes</i>
<i>from mary's meeting,</i>

28:05.284 --> 28:07.284
<i>And I saw it.</i>

28:07.286 --> 28:08.819
<i>I thought you should know.</i>

28:08.821 --> 28:11.622
<i>I never did trust</i>
<i>that pritchard.</i>

28:11.624 --> 28:13.957
<i>Was it wrong for me</i>
<i>to show you?</i>

28:13.959 --> 28:16.060
<i>No.</i>

28:16.995 --> 28:21.799
[ <i>speaking twinspeak</i> ]
what does that mean?

28:21.801 --> 28:24.535
<i>It means</i>
<i>"I don't want you to go."</i>

28:24.537 --> 28:27.204
<i>How do you say,</i>
<i>"I don't want to go"?</i>

28:27.206 --> 28:30.474
[ button clicks ]

28:30.476 --> 28:33.911
George!
I got something for you.

28:46.591 --> 28:49.259
George, what have you done?

28:49.261 --> 28:53.430
George: "my darling,
know that I tried in this life

28:53.432 --> 28:55.399
To give you everything
you ever wanted."

28:55.401 --> 28:57.134
[ crying ] no.

29:01.339 --> 29:04.007
"we are meant to be
fragile creatures.

29:04.009 --> 29:06.744
Our humanity comes
not from our strength,

29:06.746 --> 29:11.515
But from living
with this weakness."

29:11.517 --> 29:13.450
[ crying ]

29:13.452 --> 29:16.887
"there's no life
without death at its end.

29:16.889 --> 29:21.558
And I've made sure
my end will be permanent.

29:21.560 --> 29:24.094
I'm sorry.

29:24.096 --> 29:28.065
We had a beautiful life.

29:28.067 --> 29:31.101
But now...It is over."

29:34.405 --> 29:36.473
[ fire whooshes ]

29:50.288 --> 29:53.090
She was here.

29:53.092 --> 29:55.492
She called for help
from here.

29:55.494 --> 29:57.694
Play the message again.

29:59.330 --> 30:01.098
"graff"?
Hmm?

30:01.100 --> 30:02.566
Gracie sent me a text.

30:02.568 --> 30:05.435
I didn't get it
because I had my finder app on.

30:05.437 --> 30:07.271
It just came through.

30:07.273 --> 30:08.939
Graff?
Connor graff.

30:08.941 --> 30:10.440
He was gonna merge
with lookinglass

30:10.442 --> 30:11.608
If mary didn't
go into remission.

30:11.610 --> 30:13.110
He was gonna
take over the company.

30:13.112 --> 30:14.444
Why would she send me
that name?

30:14.446 --> 30:15.846
Let's find out.

30:23.621 --> 30:26.256
Just let it happen,
gracie-loo-hoo.

30:31.996 --> 30:34.064
[ indistinct conversations ]

30:36.801 --> 30:38.502
Man:
No, you cannot call her

30:38.504 --> 30:41.171
Because she has a lookinglass
phone which no longer works.

30:41.173 --> 30:43.307
Can I take a message?

30:43.309 --> 30:44.775
Okay.

30:44.777 --> 30:47.778
Uh, just a little slower,
please.

30:47.780 --> 30:50.614
The chairman
of what senate subcommittee?

30:50.616 --> 30:51.949
[ conversations stop ]

30:51.951 --> 30:53.283
Connor graff?

30:53.285 --> 30:54.451
Someone went
to a lot of trouble

30:54.453 --> 30:55.686
To make it look like
gracie ran away,

30:55.688 --> 30:57.821
But she sent duval a text
with his name.

30:57.823 --> 31:00.791
You're intimate
with connor graff.

31:00.793 --> 31:02.492
Yes.

31:02.494 --> 31:04.962
Then what would
a billionaire biotech c.E.O.

31:04.964 --> 31:06.563
Want with my daughter?

31:09.133 --> 31:11.835
Oh, god.

31:11.837 --> 31:13.904
It's not just gracie.

31:13.906 --> 31:15.672
It's all of them.

31:15.674 --> 31:17.474
They're all with connor.

31:17.476 --> 31:19.576
That must be where otto
and arthur went, to connor --

31:19.578 --> 31:21.311
And alexis, too.
They're all with connor.

31:21.313 --> 31:23.580
They <i>went,</i>
<i>but he</i> <i>took</i> her. Why?

31:23.582 --> 31:25.582
She has nothing to do
with any of this.

31:25.584 --> 31:27.751
But she does.
She's a pritchard.

31:27.753 --> 31:29.720
Gracie has
the genetic precursor.

31:29.722 --> 31:31.755
The regeneration process
would work with her.

31:31.757 --> 31:32.923
Why not take me, then?

31:32.925 --> 31:34.258
It skipped
a generation.

31:34.260 --> 31:35.926
The only two people
on the west coast

31:35.928 --> 31:38.095
With the precursor
are you and gracie.

31:38.097 --> 31:40.430
You have to go get her.
You have to go get her <i>now.</i>

31:40.432 --> 31:41.832
Where would he take her?

31:41.834 --> 31:44.067
The oncentric building has
four dedicated floors of labs.

31:44.069 --> 31:45.502
She would be there.

31:45.504 --> 31:46.937
A lot of the labs
are highly secure

31:46.939 --> 31:48.005
With limited access.

31:48.007 --> 31:50.607
Highly secure --
we'll see about that.

31:50.609 --> 31:52.576
Duval. Duval!

31:52.578 --> 31:54.011
Where exactly
are you going, kiddo?

31:54.013 --> 31:55.379
To get my daughter.

31:55.381 --> 31:57.247
Oh, yeah? Just gonna walk
in there, ask them where she is?

31:57.249 --> 31:59.716
No, I'm gonna do
what my dad would've done.

31:59.718 --> 32:02.586
I'm gonna show them my badge
first and then my fist.

32:02.588 --> 32:03.887
So come on. Let's go.

32:03.889 --> 32:05.789
Just wait.

32:05.791 --> 32:07.724
[ voice breaking ]
what is your problem here?

32:07.726 --> 32:09.092
He has gracie!

32:09.094 --> 32:10.394
Or did you miss
that part?

32:10.396 --> 32:12.029
You're not gonna get close
to a guy like connor,

32:12.031 --> 32:13.397
Even with a badge.

32:13.399 --> 32:14.765
He's surrounded by security
and lawyers.

32:14.767 --> 32:16.266
You need a warrant
just to get in the door.

32:16.268 --> 32:18.902
A warrant?
And what do I tell the judge,

32:18.904 --> 32:20.737
That connor graff
kidnapped my daughter

32:20.739 --> 32:22.306
Because she has something
in her dna

32:22.308 --> 32:25.275
That lets her get regenerated
like my dad?

32:25.277 --> 32:26.443
I said
you'd need a warrant.

32:26.445 --> 32:28.612
I didn't say anything
about a judge.

32:28.614 --> 32:32.316
I need to print --
on paper.

32:32.318 --> 32:35.252
I don't think we have
a paper printer.

32:35.254 --> 32:36.453
We're --
we're paperless.

32:36.455 --> 32:38.455
We don't have
one printer?

32:38.457 --> 32:40.057
There's one in childcare.

32:40.059 --> 32:41.725
My kid does projects on it.

32:41.727 --> 32:43.226
Bring it to otto's office.

32:45.763 --> 32:48.832
James: "this search warrant
hereby grants the sworn officer

32:48.834 --> 32:51.234
Access to any
and all property."

32:51.236 --> 32:52.769
